{"word":"ἀγωγός","slug":"ἀγωγός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγωγός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄγω'><el>ἄγω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>leading</i>, and as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a guide</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>δύναμις ἀνθρώπων ἀγωγός</el> power <i>of leading</i> men, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>leading towards</i> a point, <el>εἴς, πρός</el> or <el>ἐπί τι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>drawing forth, eliciting</i>, <el>χοαὶ νεκρῶν ἀγωγοί</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>δακρύων ἀγ.</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>attractive</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}